Russia is warning people in the Ukranian capital Kyiv to leave as they are planning a bombardment there. Some half a million people have fled the country so far. SA ambassador to Ukraine Andre Groenewald spoke with eNCA's Sally Burdett. Courtesy of #DStv403 KYIV - South African diplomats are leaving Ukraine over safety fears. SA ambassador to Ukraine Andre Groenewald confirmed to eNCA that all diplomats have been evacuated. WATCH: SA Ambassador to Ukraine speaks on help for SA's citizens Meanwhile, footage of the massive shelling Kharkiv endured has been released. Ukraine's second-biggest city has been a prime target since Russia began its invasion.